cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on Chinese semantic role labeling (SRL) and proposes a novel progressive learning model for it. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the proposed model is a machine learning model that uses neural networks. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks, which are often associated with AI. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the proposed model uses neural networks. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions a new corpus, Chinese SemBank, which may involve image or video data.
